Most Valuable Relationship Types in Real Banks

In practice, the highest ROI relationships are usually:

Relationship	Why Valuable
Trade ↔ Counterparty	Exposure aggregation
Trade ↔ Product	Risk & valuation
Position ↔ Price	NAV & PnL
Attribute ↔ Source System	Data lineage
Report ↔ Data Element	Regulatory traceability
Client ↔ Account ↔ Portfolio	Wealth & custody
Security ↔ Issuer	Concentration risk
Trade ↔ Cashflow	Liquidity
Agreement ↔ Collateral	Margin optimization
Risk Factor ↔ Position	Stress testing
Important Principle

A good financial knowledge graph is NOT:

“all tables connected together”

A good graph captures:

business meaning
causality
dependency
ownership
lifecycle
lineage
regulatory accountability

That is what makes it useful for:

AI agents
impact analysis
operations
risk
compliance
client intelligence
data governance
